\s1 The Descendants of Saul  
\b  
\li1
\v 35 Jeiel the father \f + \fr 9:35 \ft Or the founder\f* of Gibeon lived in Gibeon. His wife’s name was Maacah.   
\b  
\li1
\v 36 Abdon was his firstborn son, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab,  
\v 37 Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah, and Mikloth.   
\b  
\li1
\v 38 Mikloth was the father of Shimeam.\f + \fr 9:38 \ft Shimeam is a variant of Shimeah; see 1 Chronicles 8:32.\f* They too lived alongside their relatives in Jerusalem.   
\b  
\li1
\v 39 Ner was the father of Kish, Kish was the father of Saul, and Saul was the father of Jonathan, Malchishua, Abinadab, and Esh-baal.   
\b  
\li1
\v 40 The son of Jonathan:  
\b  
\li2 Merib-baal, who was the father of Micah.   
\b  
\li1
\v 41 The sons of Micah:  
\b  
\li2 Pithon, Melech, Tahrea, and Ahaz.\f + \fr 9:41 \ft Vulgate and Syriac (see also LXX and 1 Chronicles 8:35); Hebrew Pithon, Melech, and Tahrea; note that Tahrea is a variant of Tarea.\f*   
\b  
\li2
\v 42 Ahaz was the father of Jarah; Jarah \f + \fr 9:42 \ft Most Hebrew manuscripts; some Hebrew manuscripts and LXX Jadah; Jadah; note that Jarah and Jadah are variants of Jehoaddah; see 1 Chronicles 8:36.\f* was the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri; and Zimri was the father of Moza.  
\v 43 Moza was the father of Binea. Rephaiah \f + \fr 9:43 \ft Rephaiah is a variant of Raphah; see 1 Chronicles 8:37.\f* was his son, Elasah his son, and Azel his son.   
\b  
\li1
\v 44 And Azel had six sons, and these were their names:  
\b  
\li2 Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. These were the sons of Azel.   
