\m Asaph, \w Jeduthun|strong="H3038"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w Heman|strong="H1968"\w* \w were|strong="H3027"\w* \w under|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w direction|strong="H3027"\w* \w of|strong="H4428"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w*.  
\v 7 \w Together|strong="H5973"\w* \w with|strong="H5973"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* relatives, \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w trained|strong="H3925"\w* \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w skillful|strong="H3925"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w songs|strong="H7892"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w*, \w they|strong="H3068"\w* \w numbered|strong="H4557"\w* 288.  
\v 8 They \w cast|strong="H5307"\w* \w lots|strong="H1486"\w* \w for|strong="H5973"\w* \w their|strong="H5307"\w* \w duties|strong="H4931"\w*, \w young|strong="H6996"\w* \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w old|strong="H1419"\w* \w alike|strong="H5973"\w*, teacher \w as|strong="H5980"\w* \w well|strong="H5980"\w* \w as|strong="H5980"\w* \w pupil|strong="H8527"\w*.   
\b  
\li1
\v 9 The first lot, which was for Asaph, fell to Joseph, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;\f + \fr 25:9 \ft See LXX and the total in verse 7; Hebrew does not include his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;\f*  
\b  
\li1 the second to Gedaliah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 10 the third to Zaccur, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 11 the fourth to Izri,\f + \fr 25:11 \ft Izri is a variant of Zeri; see verse 3.\f* his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 12 the fifth to Nethaniah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 13 the sixth to Bukkiah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 14 the seventh to Jesarelah,\f + \fr 25:14 \ft Jesarelah is a variant of Asarelah; see verse 2.\f* his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 15 the eighth to Jeshaiah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 16 the ninth to Mattaniah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 17 the tenth to Shimei, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 18 the eleventh to Azarel,\f + \fr 25:18 \ft Azarel is a variant of Uzziel; see verse 4.\f* his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 19 the twelfth to Hashabiah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 20 the thirteenth to Shubael, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 21 the fourteenth to Mattithiah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 22 the fifteenth to Jeremoth,\f + \fr 25:22 \ft Jeremoth is a variant of Jerimoth; see verse 4.\f* his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 23 the sixteenth to Hananiah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 24 the seventeenth to Joshbekashah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 25 the eighteenth to Hanani, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 26 the nineteenth to Mallothi, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 27 the twentieth to Eliathah, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 28 the twenty-first to Hothir, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 29 the twenty-second to Giddalti, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 30 the twenty-third to Mahazioth, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all;   
\b  
\li1
\v 31 and the twenty-fourth to Romamti-ezer, his sons, and his brothers—12 in all.   
\c 26  
\s1 The Divisions of the Gatekeepers  
\m
\v 1 These \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H4480"\w* \w divisions|strong="H4256"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H4480"\w* \w gatekeepers|strong="H7778"\w*:  
\b  
\li1 From the Korahites: Meshelemiah son of Kore, one of the sons of Asaph.   
\b  
\li1
\v 2 Meshelemiah had sons: Zechariah the firstborn, Jediael the second, Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth,  
\v 3 Elam the fifth, Jehohanan the sixth, and Eliehoenai the seventh.   
\b  
\li1
\v 4 And Obed-edom also had sons: Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second, Joah the third, Sachar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth,  
\v 5 Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, and Peullethai the eighth. For God had blessed Obed-edom.   
\b  
\li1
\v 6 Also to his son Shemaiah were born sons who ruled over their families because they were strong, capable men.  
\v 7 Shemaiah’s sons were Othni, Rephael, Obed, and Elzabad; his brothers were Elihu and Semachiah, also capable men.  
\v 8 All these were descendants of Obed-edom; they and their sons and brothers were capable men with strength to do the work—62 in all from Obed-edom.   
\b  
\li1
\v 9 Meshelemiah also had sons and brothers who were capable men—18 in all.   
\b  
\li1
\v 10 Hosah the Merarite also had sons: Shimri the first (although he was not the firstborn, his father had appointed him as the first),  
\v 11 Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the third, and Zechariah the fourth. The sons and brothers of Hosah numbered 13 in all.   
\b  
\m
\v 12 \w These|strong="H1004"\w* \w divisions|strong="H4256"\w* \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w gatekeepers|strong="H7778"\w*, through \w their|strong="H3068"\w* \w chief|strong="H7218"\w* \w men|strong="H1397"\w*, \w had|strong="H3068"\w* \w duties|strong="H4931"\w* \w for|strong="H3068"\w* \w ministering|strong="H8334"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w house|strong="H1004"\w* \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w*, \w just|strong="H5980"\w* \w as|strong="H3068"\w* \w their|strong="H3068"\w* brothers \w did|strong="H3068"\w*.  
\v 13 \w They|strong="H8179"\w* \w cast|strong="H5307"\w* \w lots|strong="H1486"\w* \w for|strong="H1004"\w* \w each|strong="H8179"\w* \w gate|strong="H8179"\w*, according \w to|strong="H1004"\w* \w their|strong="H5307"\w* \w families|strong="H1004"\w*, \w young|strong="H6996"\w* \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w old|strong="H1419"\w* alike.   
\b  
\li1
\v 14 The lot for the East Gate fell to Shelemiah.\f + \fr 26:14 \ft Shelemiah is a variant of Meshelemiah; see verse 2.\f*  
\b  
\li1 Then lots were cast for his son Zechariah, a wise counselor, and the lot for the North Gate fell to him.   
\b  
\li1
\v 15 The lot for the South Gate fell to Obed-edom, and the lot for the storehouses to his sons.   
\b  
\li1
\v 16 The lots for the West Gate and the Shallecheth Gate on the ascending highway \f + \fr 26:16 \ft Or on the upper road\f* fell to Shuppim and Hosah.  
\b  
\m \w There|strong="H5927"\w* \w were|strong="H8179"\w* guards stationed \w at|strong="H5927"\w* \w every|strong="H5927"\w* \w watch|strong="H4929"\w*.  
\v 17 \w Each|strong="H3117"\w* \w day|strong="H3117"\w* \w there|strong="H3117"\w* \w were|strong="H3881"\w* \w six|strong="H8337"\w* \w Levites|strong="H3881"\w* \w on|strong="H3117"\w* \w the|strong="H3117"\w* \w east|strong="H4217"\w*, four \w on|strong="H3117"\w* \w the|strong="H3117"\w* \w north|strong="H6828"\w*, four \w on|strong="H3117"\w* \w the|strong="H3117"\w* \w south|strong="H5045"\w*, \w and|strong="H3117"\w* \w two|strong="H8147"\w* \w pairs|strong="H8147"\w* \w at|strong="H3117"\w* \w the|strong="H3117"\w* storehouse.  
\v 18 As \w for|strong="H8147"\w* \w the|strong="H8147"\w* court \f + \fr 26:18 \ft Hebrew parbar; twice in this verse\f* on \w the|strong="H8147"\w* \w west|strong="H4628"\w*, there \w were|strong="H8147"\w* four \w at|strong="H8147"\w* \w the|strong="H8147"\w* \w highway|strong="H4546"\w* \w and|strong="H8147"\w* \w two|strong="H8147"\w* \w at|strong="H8147"\w* \w the|strong="H8147"\w* court.   
\b  
\m
\v 19 These \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w divisions|strong="H4256"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w gatekeepers|strong="H7778"\w* \w who|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w descendants|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Korah|strong="H7145"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Merari|strong="H4847"\w*.   
\s1 The Treasurers, Officers, and Judges  
\b  
\m
\v 20 \w Now|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H5921"\w* fellow \w Levites|strong="H3881"\w* \w were|strong="H3881"\w* \f + \fr 26:20 \ft LXX; Hebrew As for the Levites, Ahijah was\f* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w charge|strong="H5921"\w* \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* treasuries \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w house|strong="H1004"\w* \w of|strong="H1004"\w* God \w and|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* treasuries \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w dedicated|strong="H6944"\w* \w things|strong="H6944"\w*.  
\v 21 \w From|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w descendants|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Ladan|strong="H3936"\w*, \w who|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w Gershonites|strong="H1649"\w* through \w Ladan|strong="H3936"\w* \f + \fr 26:21 \ft Ladan is a variant of Libni; see 1 Chronicles 6:17.\f* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w heads|strong="H7218"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w families|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Ladan|strong="H3936"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w Gershonite|strong="H1649"\w*, \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w Jehieli|strong="H3172"\w*,\f + \fr 26:21 \ft Jehieli is a variant of Jehiel; also in verse 22; see 1 Chronicles 23:8.\f*  
\v 22 \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Jehieli|strong="H3172"\w*, \w Zetham|strong="H2241"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H3068"\w* brother \w Joel|strong="H3100"\w*. \w They|strong="H3068"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w charge|strong="H5921"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* treasuries \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w house|strong="H1004"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w*.   
\b  
\m
\v 23 From the \w Amramites|strong="H6020"\w*, the \w Izharites|strong="H3325"\w*, the \w Hebronites|strong="H2276"\w*, and the \w Uzzielites|strong="H5817"\w*:   
\b  
\li1
\v 24 Shebuel, a descendant of Gershom son of Moses, was the officer in charge of the treasuries.  
\v 25 His relatives through Eliezer included Rehabiah his son, Jeshaiah \f + \fr 26:25 \ft Jeshaiah is a variant of Isshiah; see 1 Chronicles 24:21.\f* his son, Joram his son, Zichri his son, and Shelomith his son.  
\v 26 This Shelomith and his brothers were in charge of all the treasuries for the things dedicated by King David, by the heads of families who were the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, and by the army commanders.  
\v 27 They had dedicated some of the plunder from their battles to the repair of the house of the LORD.  
\v 28 Everything that had been dedicated by Samuel the seer, Saul son of Kish, Abner son of Ner, and Joab son of Zeruiah, along with everything else that was dedicated, was under the care of Shelomith and his brothers.   
\b  
\li1
\v 29 From the Izrahites, Chenaniah and his sons had the outside duties \f + \fr 26:29 \ft Or the duties outside (the temple) or the duties outside (Jerusalem)\f* as officers and judges over Israel.   
\b  
\li1
\v 30 From the Hebronites, Hashabiah and his relatives, 1,700 capable men, had charge of the affairs of Israel west of the Jordan for all the work of the LORD and for the service of the king.  
\v 31 As for the Hebronites, Jerijah \f + \fr 26:31 \ft Jerijah is a variant of Jeriah; see 1 Chronicles 23:19.\f* was the chief of the Hebronites, according to the genealogies of his ancestors. In the fortieth year of David’s reign the records were searched, and strong, capable men were found among the Hebronites at Jazer in Gilead.  
\v 32 Among Jerijah’s relatives there were 2,700 capable men who were heads of families. King David appointed them over the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh for every matter pertaining to God and to the affairs of the king.   
\c 27  
\s1 Twelve Captains for Twelve Months  
\m
\v 1 \w This|strong="H1697"\w* \w is|strong="H1697"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w list|strong="H4557"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w Israelites|strong="H3478"\w*—\w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w heads|strong="H7218"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w families|strong="H1121"\w*, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w commanders|strong="H8269"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* thousands \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w hundreds|strong="H3967"\w*, \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w officers|strong="H7860"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w served|strong="H8334"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w every|strong="H3605"\w* \w matter|strong="H1697"\w* \w concerning|strong="H1697"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w divisions|strong="H4256"\w* \w on|strong="H3318"\w* rotating military \w duty|strong="H1697"\w* \w each|strong="H3605"\w* \w month|strong="H2320"\w* \w throughout|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w year|strong="H8141"\w*. \w There|strong="H1697"\w* \w were|strong="H3478"\w* 24,000 \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w each|strong="H3605"\w* \w division|strong="H4256"\w*:   
\b  
\li1
\v 2 Jashobeam son of Zabdiel was in charge of the first division, which was assigned the first month. There were 24,000 men in his division.  
\v 3 He was a descendant of Perez and chief of all the army commanders for the first month.   
\b  
\li1
\v 4 Dodai \f + \fr 27:4 \ft Dodai is a variant of Dodo; see 2 Samuel 23:9.\f* the Ahohite was in charge of the division for the second month, and Mikloth was the leader. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 5 The third army commander, as chief for the third month, was Benaiah son of Jehoiada the priest. There were 24,000 men in his division.  
\v 6 This Benaiah was mighty among the Thirty and was over the Thirty, and his son Ammizabad was in charge of his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 7 The fourth, for the fourth month, was Joab’s brother Asahel, and his son Zebadiah was commander after him. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 8 The fifth, for the fifth month, was the commander Shamhuth \f + \fr 27:8 \ft Shamhuth is a variant of Shammoth or Shammah; see 1 Chronicles 11:27 and 2 Samuel 23:25.\f* the Izrahite. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 9 The sixth, for the sixth month, was Ira son of Ikkesh the Tekoite. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 10 The seventh, for the seventh month, was Helez the Pelonite, an Ephraimite. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 11 The eighth, for the eighth month, was Sibbecai the Hushathite, a Zerahite. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 12 The ninth, for the ninth month, was Abiezer the Anathothite, a Benjamite. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 13 The tenth, for the tenth month, was Maharai the Netophathite, a Zerahite. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 14 The eleventh, for the eleventh month, was Benaiah the Pirathonite, an Ephraimite. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\b  
\li1
\v 15 The twelfth, for the twelfth month, was Heldai \f + \fr 27:15 \ft Heldai is a variant of Heled; see 1 Chronicles 11:30 and 2 Samuel 23:29.\f* the Netophathite, from the family of Othniel. There were 24,000 men in his division.   
\s1 The Leaders of the Twelve Tribes  
\b  
\m
\v 16 These \w officers|strong="H5057"\w* \w were|strong="H3478"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w charge|strong="H5921"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w tribes|strong="H7626"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*:  
\b  
\li1 Over the Reubenites was Eliezer son of Zichri;  
\b  
\li1 over the Simeonites was Shephatiah son of Maacah;   
\b  
\li1
\v 17 over Levi was Hashabiah son of Kemuel;  
\b  
\li1 over Aaron was Zadok;   
\b  
\li1
\v 18 over Judah was Elihu, one of David’s brothers;  
\b  
\li1 over Issachar was Omri son of Michael;   
\b  
\li1
\v 19 over Zebulun was Ishmaiah son of Obadiah;  
\b  
\li1 over Naphtali was Jerimoth son of Azriel;   
\b  
\li1
\v 20 over the Ephraimites was Hoshea son of Azaziah;  
\b  
\li1 over one of the half-tribes of Manasseh was Joel son of Pedaiah;   
\b  
\li1
\v 21 over the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead was Iddo son of Zechariah;  
\b  
\li1 over Benjamin was Jaasiel son of Abner;   
\q1
\v 22 \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w over|strong="H8269"\w* \w Dan|strong="H1835"\w* \w was|strong="H3478"\w* \w Azarel|strong="H5832"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Jeroham|strong="H3395"\w*.  
\b  
\m These \w were|strong="H3478"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w leaders|strong="H8269"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w tribes|strong="H7626"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*.   
\b  
\m
\v 23 \w David|strong="H1732"\w* \w did|strong="H3478"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w count|strong="H8141"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* aged \w twenty|strong="H6242"\w* \w or|strong="H3808"\w* \w under|strong="H4295"\w*, \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w* \w had|strong="H3068"\w* said \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w He|strong="H3588"\w* \w would|strong="H3068"\w* \w make|strong="H7235"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* \w as|strong="H3068"\w* \w numerous|strong="H7235"\w* \w as|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w stars|strong="H3556"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w sky|strong="H8064"\w*.  
\v 24 \w Joab|strong="H3097"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Zeruiah|strong="H6870"\w* \w began|strong="H2490"\w* \w to|strong="H3478"\w* \w count|strong="H4487"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w but|strong="H3808"\w* \w did|strong="H3478"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w finish|strong="H3615"\w*. \w For|strong="H5921"\w* \w because|strong="H5921"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w this|strong="H2063"\w* census \w wrath|strong="H7110"\w* \w came|strong="H1961"\w* \w upon|strong="H5921"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w number|strong="H4557"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w entered|strong="H5927"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w Book|strong="H1697"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w Chronicles|strong="H1697"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w King|strong="H4428"\w* \w David|strong="H1732"\w*.   
\s1 David’s Various Overseers  
\b  
\li1
\v 25 Azmaveth son of Adiel was in charge of the royal storehouses.  
\b  
\li1 Jonathan son of Uzziah was in charge of the storehouses in the country, in the cities, in the villages, and in the fortresses.   
\b  
\li1
\v 26 Ezri son of Chelub was in charge of the workers in the fields who tilled the soil.   
\b  
\li1
\v 27 Shimei the Ramathite was in charge of the vineyards.  
\b  
\li1 Zabdi the Shiphmite was in charge of the produce of the vineyards for the wine vats.   
\b  
\li1
\v 28 Baal-hanan the Gederite was in charge of the olive and sycamore trees in the foothills.\f + \fr 27:28 \ft Hebrew Shephelah or lowlands; that is, the western foothills of Judea\f*  
\b  
\li1 Joash was in charge of the stores of olive oil.   
\b  
\li1
\v 29 Shitrai the Sharonite was in charge of the herds grazing in Sharon.  
\b  
\li1 Shaphat son of Adlai was in charge of the herds in the valleys.   
\b  
\li1
\v 30 Obil the Ishmaelite was in charge of the camels.  
\b  
\li1 Jehdeiah the Meronothite was in charge of the donkeys.   
\b  
\li1
\v 31 Jaziz the Hagrite was in charge of the flocks.  
\b  
\li1 All these officials were in charge of King David’s property.   
\s1 The Counselors  
\b  
\li1
\v 32 David’s uncle Jonathan was a counselor; he was a man of insight and a scribe.  
\b  
\li1 Jehiel son of Hachmoni attended to the sons of the king.   
\b  
\li1
\v 33 Ahithophel was the king’s counselor.  
\b  
\li1 Hushai the Archite was the king’s friend.   
\b  
\li1
\v 34 Ahithophel was succeeded by Jehoiada son of Benaiah, then by Abiathar.  
\b  
\li1 Joab was the commander of the king’s army.   
